metadata.name: Little Window
metadata.description:
The sunshine has a pleasant way
Of shining on us all the day,
It makes the little window bright,
And fills the room with pretty light.

We were in a house under construction. The sun was coming through a little roof window. I used strips of tape to form these shadow lines. Melissa laid down on this white sheet that was there to protect the floor from paint. I told her what pose to take and triggered the camera.

40x60cm Fine Art print and signed version may be requested for the collector.
